### **Given:**

- Building height: 40 floors
- Each floor is 5 meters tall → Total height = $ 40 \times 5 = 200 $ meters
- Elevator acceleration/deceleration = $ 1 \, \text{m/s}^2 $
- Maximum speed = $ 5 \, \text{m/s} $

